When Credit Repository Source Type is set to Other, enter its value in this data element.
This indicator is set to Y when the Credit Response Alert Message contains information which may be considered adverse and may require further investigation or other action.
Describes the general category of the alert message. This allows for automated processing by systems reading the credit alert messages.
When Credit Response Alert Message Category Type is set to Other, enter its value in this data element.
This is the code value associated with the Credit Response Alert Message Text and/or Credit Response Alert Message Type.

This element identifies the name of the source for the code values used in the Credit Response Alert Message Code. The enumeration definition identifies the source document and name of the table that contains the code values.
When the Credit Response Alert Message Code Source Type has a value of Other, this element identifies the name of the source for the code values used in the Credit Response Alert Message Code.
Text of the alert message.
Lists the name of the repository bureau or other product that generated the alert message.
When Credit Response Alert Message Type is set to Other, enter its value in this data element.

The elements in this container identify a variety of data values and option parameters about the credit response, such as the credit report identifier, first issued and last updated dates, report type, etc.

Identifies which system of Manner Of Payment (MOP) rating codes is in the credit report. If Other is selected, then the name of the coding system will appear in the Credit Rating Code Type Other Description.
If the Credit Rating Code Type is set to Other, enter its description in this data attribute.
Date and time the referenced credit report was first issued.
A reference number assigned by the credit bureau to a specific credit report. This report number is also referenced when a Reissue, Upgrade, or Status Query of an existing report is requested.
The date and time that the referenced credit report was last updated or revised.
This element indicates how duplicate data from multiple sources is handled on a credit report.
Uniquely identifies a specific instance of a credit report transaction.

The type of credit report that was requested or produced. Most common types are Merged report (data from credit data repositories is merged), and RMCR (Residential Mortgage Credit Report - contains verified liabilities, employment, etc.).
When Credit Report Type is set to Other, enter its description in this element.
Identifies which system of rating codes is used within the Credit Liability Payment Pattern Data text string.
When Payment Pattern Rating Code Type has a value of Other, this element identifies the rating code system applied to the Credit Liability Payment Pattern Data text string.

The type of credit report that was requested or produced. Most common types are Merged report (data from credit data repositories is merged), and RMCR (Residential Mortgage Credit Report - contains verified liabilities, employment, etc.).
When Credit Report Type is set to Other, enter its description in this element.
If true, indicates the credit report was based on the input from a single credit repository. Also known as a single in-file credit report.
Indicates whether a Credit Repository Source is available. If a Credit Repository Source is available then the source can be provided in Credit Repository Source Type.
This element describes the source of the credit file, Equifax, Experian, Trans Union or Unspecified if the specific sources are not specified.
When Credit Repository Source Type is set to Other, enter its value in this data element.

An enumerated list that describes the general type or purpose of a credit score model. This allows LOS systems to extract scores by a more general category, without having to know the specific score model names.
When Credit Score Category Type is set to "Other", enter its value in this data element.
A value from a MISMO prescribed list that represents a specific version, release of a Credit Score Category Type.
A free-form text field that specifies the enumeration when the value of Other is used for Credit Score Category Version Type.
Date that the referenced credit score was produced.
A value from a MISMO defined list that identifies the reason why a credit score could not be generated.

This indicator is set to True when the Credit Risk Score Value of the borrower or guarantor was negatively affected by the presence of credit inquiry records on their credit report. There may be FACT Act compliance requirements related to this alert message.
Identifies a characteristic of the Credit Score that impairs its effectiveness as an indicator of credit risk.
A free-form text field used to collect additional information when Other is selected for Credit Score Impairment Type.
A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies the score algorithm model name used to produce the referenced credit risk score.
When the Credit Score Model Name Type is set to Other, this element holds the description.
A detailed description of how the credit score compares to the scores of other consumers.
The percentile that the parties credit score is in comparison to all consumers.
Numeric credit score resulting from credit evaluation model.

When true, indicates that the Credit Score Value is the recommended value chosen from a collection of credit scores for a single borrower or guarantor, based on criteria as defined by trading partners. For example, this may be used to identify the middle Credit Score.

Identifies a reason or factor that reduced the Credit Score Value from its maximum possible value.

Factors of the borrower's or guarantor's credit which give context to the referenced credit score. The factor is normally a numeric code. The Credit Score Factor Text contains the text for the factor code.
